# Local: copy to `.env.local`. Production (e.g. Render): Dashboard → your Web Service → Environment → Environment Variables (then redeploy).

# --- Spotify Web API (Client Credentials) ---
# Used when Settings → Metadata provider = Spotify: Search tracks/playlists, playlist import, some home rails.
# 1. Open https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard → Create app (any name).
# 2. In the app: Settings → Client ID and "View client secret".
# 3. You do NOT need a redirect URI for this app (server-side client_credentials only).
# 4. On Render: add both variables exactly as below (no quotes). Redeploy so the server picks them up.
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Optional: if omitted, Next uses the host from the request. Set only if you have a special proxy setup.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=
